<TEXT>
<P>
 The power of the Olympics? 
</P>
<P>
 NYNEX, a U.S. luge sponsor, is running a two-week commercial in the 
Northeastern states listing an 800 phone number for youngsters interested in 
luge. 
</P>
<P>
 "We've had 2,500 calls in the first week," Ron Rossi, executive director of 
the U.S. Luge Federation, said. "We have only two phone lines. That's nonstop 
ringing." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Gerhard Rainer, a 33-year-old Innsbruck policeman and driver of Austria's 
two-man bobsled, tested positive for metandienon, a growth hormone, and was 
expelled from the Olympics. Kurt Einberger, driver of Austria's four-man sled, 
will replace Rainer. ROSS NEWHAN 
</P>
