<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; CANYONS BEATS HARBOR ON A WALKOVER, 7-6 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Scott Minkler drew a bases-loaded walk with two out in the 10th inning to give 
College of the Canyons a 7-6 victory over Harbor in a nonconference game 
Tuesday at Wilmington. 
</P>
<P>
 J.T. Billingslea's three-run home run in the sixth gave Canyons (3-0) a 5-2 
lead. Harbor tied it, 6-6, with two runs in the eighth. 
</P>
<P>
 R.J. Fenolio and Ari Jacobs each had three hits for Canyons. 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran 8, Concordia 4 -- A six-run second inning, fueled by two-run 
singles from Ray Arvizu and Scott Sebbo, helped the Kingsmen (4-1) to a 
nonconference victory at Thousand Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
 Sam Arroyo (1-0) pitched three innings for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 The Master's 7, CS San Bernardino 6 -- Matt Henzie's one-out, bases-loaded 
double drove in two runs in the eighth to propel the Mustangs to victory in the 
nonconference game at Newhall. 
</P>
<P>
 Henzie had two hits and drove in three runs for Master's (3-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley 8, Ventura 7 -- Catcher Jack Cox hit a solo home run in the 
bottom of the seventh to give the Marauders a 7-6 lead and they held on for a 
nonconference victory at Antelope Valley (4-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Pirate center fielder Jamal Nichols went three for four, drove in three runs 
and stole three bases. 
</P>
<P>
 Brandon Yount went three for three, including a home run and a double, scored 
twice and drove in three runs for the Marauders. 
</P>
<P>
 Valley 8, L.A. City 8 -- The Cubs scored five runs in the top of the ninth 
inning to tie the nonconference game, 8-8, and the game was called due to 
darkness in the 11th at Valley (1-4-1. SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley 4-0, El Camino 0-2 -- Heather Myer (1-0) pitched a two-hitter 
and Jody Snelling had four hits and three RBIs to lead Antelope Valley (1-1) to 
victory in the first game of the nonconference doubleheader at Torrance. 
</P>
<P>
 The Marauders were held to three hits in the second game. WOMEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 The Master's 63, Whittier 49 -- Deb Prociw had 29 points, five rebounds, four 
assists and four steals for the Mustangs in a nonconference game at Newhall. 
</P>
<P>
 Prociw hit 11 of 19 shots, including six of 10 from three-point range, for 
Master's (5-15). 
</P>
<P>
 Kim DeVries added 19 points and 17 rebounds for the Mustangs. 
</P>
<P>
 Occidental 75, Cal Lutheran 66 -- Diana Cortez and Kelli McCaskill each scored 
17 points as the Regals (6-13) dropped a SCIAC game at Occidental. COLLEGE 
SWIMMING 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Collegiate Swimming Conference championships -- Freshman Dawn Burton 
and sophomore Sara Cassady gave Cal State Northridge a one-two finish in the 
women's three-meter diving event at Belmont Plaza in Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Burton totaled 494.60 points and Cassady had 437.15. 
</P>
