PREP BASKETBALL PLAYOFFS; LYNWOOD SEES TOO MUCH OF ALHAMBRA'S CONTRERAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Center Mike Contreras scored 23 points and had 22 rebounds to lead Alhambra to 
a 43-41 overtime upset of 19th-ranked Lynwood in a Division I-AA first-round 
playoff game Tuesday at Alhambra. 
</P>
<P>
 Contreras scored all nine overtime points for the Moors, who improved to 15-10 
and will play Ayala (21-4) in a second-round game on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Lynwood (17-9) finished the regular season in third place in the San Gabriel 
Valley League to advance to the playoffs. The Moors finished in second place in 
the Almont League. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 1 Santa Ana Mater Dei 94, Irvine 45 -- Schea Cotton scored 30 points to 
lead the Monarchs (27-0) to a Division I-A first-round victory over the 
Vaqueros (13-13) at Santa Ana. 
</P>
