<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: BOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Damien Cantrell 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Santa Clara 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Cantrell played on the junior varsity last season, then 
grew four inches to 6-foot-4 over the summer. He has exceeded all expectations 
with averages of 21 points and 8.2 rebounds for the Saints (15-7).He averaged 
23.6 points and 10.8 rebounds in Frontier League play as the Saints extended 
their league winning streak to 84 games. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Cantrell had 32 points and 10 rebounds in a 74-51 victory 
over Calabasas and 31 points and 14 rebounds in a 77-58 victory over Nordhoff. 
Against Calabasas, Cantrell made 13 of 18 shots from the field, including four 
of five three-pointers. Lou Cvijanovich, Santa Clara's coach of 36 seasons, 
compares Cantrell with his best players, including UCLA's Shon Tarver and 
former Washington State player Joe Wallace. Said Lou Cvijanovich: "He can put 
the ball on the floor and he can shoot the three as good as anybody." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Profile 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA021694-0103 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 013937 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
