<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 12; Column 4 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
137 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: GIRLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Julie Wastell 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Newbury Park 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Junior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: The 5-foot-7 guard is averaging 10.8 points and 4.4 
assists and has been the floor leader for the Panthers, who are 21-4 and placed 
second in the Marmonte League with a 12-2 record. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Wastell hit the game-winning shot with seven seconds to play 
in last Tuesday night's 39-37 victory over Channel Islands, ranked third in the 
Southern Section Division I. She finished with 13 points as the Panthers ended 
the Raiders' 19-game winning streak.Wastell also had 21 points, including three 
three-point baskets in the first half, during Newbury Park's victory over Royal 
on Thursday night. "She's the key to the ballclub," Coach Nori Parvin said. 
"Without her, we can't do the things we've been doing out there." 
</P>
