<HEADLINE>
<P>
CSUN SHORES UP DEFENSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE HISERMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cal State Northridge football team has added some of the defensive help it 
desperately needs. 
</P>
<P>
 Mark Venturine, a former starter at Oregon State, and three others have 
enrolled at Northridge, the school announced Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Venturine, 5-foot-11, 180 pounds, was a starting cornerback for Oregon State 
his freshman and junior seasons. The senior from Burbank is expected to earn a 
spot in Northridge's lineup as a defensive back and a kick returner. 
</P>
<P>
 The Matadors (4-6 last season) also have added three junior college transfers. 
</P>
<P>
 Linebackers Michael Greslie II and Joseph Pierro are attending classes at 
Northridge. Alberto Contreras, another linebacker, said last week he was 
joining the Matadors. 
</P>
<P>
 Greslie (6-3, 225) and Contreras (6-0, 233) played for Valley College last 
season. Pierro (6-1, 215) played for Fresno City College. MIKE HISERMAN 
</P>
