<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Julie Murdent 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West, Fr. 
</P>
<P>
 Basketball / Center 
</P>
<P>
 The first time Golden West played Orange Coast in an Orange Empire Conference 
game this season, the Rustlers had a simple plan -- get the ball inside to 
Murdent.She responded with a season-high 24 points as Golden West won in 
overtime, 79-71. When the teams met last Wednesday the plan was the same. This 
time Murdent, from Fountain Valley High School, had 22 points in a 65-55 
victory. She also had 17 rebounds and four blocked shots. She came back to 
score 18 points and get 11 rebounds as Golden West clinched the conference 
title with a 91-68 victory over Saddleback Friday. Other notables: 
</P>
<P>
 * Jennifer Johnson, Cypress, had 18 points and seven rebounds as the Chargers 
beat Saddleback, 79-46. 
</P>
<P>
 * Kim Stiglbauer, Cypress, pitched a two-hit shutout as the Chargers beat 
Palomar, 2-0, in the title game of the Rancho Santiago tournament. 
