<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: MEET YOUR SUPERVISORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Times Staff Writer Susan Christian 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 If you have questions for local officials about such topics as the county's 
economic climate, business regulations and public safety, you'll get a chance 
to voice your concerns Feb. 23 at the Orange County Chamber of Commerce & 
Industry's annual "Meet Your Supervisor" luncheon. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will feature a panel of Orange County's supervisors who will field 
questions from the audience. It will take place at the Westin South Coast Plaza 
hotel in Costa Mesa. A reception begins at 11:30 a.m., with lunch at noon. Cost 
is $28.50 for chamber members and $33.50 for non-members. 
</P>
<P>
 For reservations and further information, call (714) 634-2900. 
