<P>
 Earthquakes have shown that the weak links in California's freeway system are 
its overpasses and bridges. Out of a statewide total of 12,000 freeway bridges, 
Caltrans officials have decided that 1,313 should be strengthened, and work on 
251 of them has been completed. In Los Angeles County, there are 2,523 freeway 
bridges, with 716 scheduled for retrofitting and 115 completed. The map shows 
the status of remedial work on major Southland routes. 
