<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARRESTS MADE IN ROBBERY, BURGLARIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police arrested an armed Texas man Monday on suspicion of armed robbery, 
several burglaries and a hit-and-run accident, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Roy David Broker, 30, and a companion, Teri Ann Bertsche, 30, of Costa Mesa, 
were taken into custody in the parking lot of a motel in the 11700 block of 
Beach Boulevard about 5:30 p.m., according to the Orange County Sheriff's 
Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputy Angel Andrade said he spotted a vehicle in the parking lot that matched 
a broadcast description of the brown 1977 Ford Grenada thought to be involved 
in an armed robbery of a sandwich shop in Westminster 10 minutes earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 The deputy held the couple at gunpoint but without incident until backup units 
arrived. Deputies said Broker had a .32-caliber revolver. 
</P>
<P>
 Bertsche also was arrested on suspicion of robbery, and both were booked into 
the Orange County Jail. 
</P>
<P>
 Broker is considered a suspect in several other robberies and a hit-and-run 
accident in Westminster, and several burglaries in Newport Beach, according to 
Lt. Dan Martini of the Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
</TEXT>
