<P>
WORLD WATCH: EU TO FINE STEELMAKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The European Commission is due to fine 17 steel companies Wednesday on grounds 
they colluded illegally to fix prices, a senior official for the commission 
said.Ironically, the fines will be announced the day after the commission meets 
industry representatives to seek cuts in production capacity as part of an 
attempt to haul the beleaguered sector out of trouble. Among the firms in line 
for fines are Arbed, British Steel, Unimetal, Saarstahl, Ferdofin, Fried 
Krupp-Hoesch, NMH Stahlwerke and Fundia Norske, the official said. Under 
European Union antitrust rules, the commission can fine firms up to 10% of 
their annual sales revenue. 
</P>
