<TEXT>
<P>
 Triconex Corp.: The Irvine company, which develops safety and control systems 
and supplies turbine and compressor control systems, posted a profit of $5.6 
million, or $1.08 a share, for 1993.That was up 27% from earnings of $4.4 
million, or 91 cents a share, for 1992. Sales rose 35% to $39.2 million from 
$29 million. For the fourth quarter, profit showed a 23% gain to $1.6 million, 
or 30 cents a share, from $1.3 million, or 24 cents a share, for the same 
period a year earlier. Three-month revenue rose 45% to $11.3 million from $7.8 
million. The results include Triconex's consolidation since June 1 with Tri-Sen 
Systems Inc., a Texas producer of digital turbo-machinery control systems. 
</P>
