<TEXT>
<P>
 Pinnacle Micro Inc.: The Irvine manufacturer of optical storage systems 
reported a profit of $2.6 million for 1993, compared to earnings of $1.3 
million for 1992.Sales increased 71% to $39.2 million from $22.9 million. 
Profit for the fourth quarter totaled $653,100, compared to earnings of 
$836,000 for the same period a year earlier. Three-month sales were $11.2 
million, up from $7.8 million. Effective July 1, the company changed its method 
of incorporation. Pro forma earnings per share were 42 cents a share for 1993, 
compared to 22 cents a share for the previous 12 months. Fourth-quarter 
earnings were 12 cents a share for 1993 and 14 cents a share for 1992. 
</P>
