<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Licklider Group: The private investment company said Tuesday that it plans 
to invest up to $6 million in ThriftyTel Inc., a provider of long-distance 
telephone service. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the tentative agreement, the group would invest $3 million for a 25% 
stake in ThriftyTel and would have an option to buy another 25% for $3 million. 
</P>
<P>
 William J. Kettle, chairman of Garden Grove-based ThriftyTel, and another 
shareholder will grant their voting rights to the Licklider Group for two years 
as a condition of the investment. 
</P>
<P>
 The Licklider Group, also based in Garden Grove, is headed by Rex Licklider, 
the founder and former chairman and chief executive officer of Com Systems 
Inc., a long-distance telephone service company headquartered in Westlake 
Village. 
</P>
</TEXT>
