<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Enertech: The Brea company, which supplies parts to nuclear power plants, said 
Tuesday that it won a $2-million award as a result of arbitration proceedings 
in a dispute with an Illinois company. 
</P>
<P>
 Enertech sued C&S Valve Co. of Westmont, Ill., several years ago for alleged 
breach of contract, said Enertech spokeswoman Arlene Corkhill. C&S, which 
countersued, allegedly broke an agreement to supply valves to Enertech. 
</P>
<P>
 The companies agreed to submit to out-of-court arbitration moderated by the 
American Arbitration Assn. The arbitration was decided in favor of Enertech and 
the countersuit against it was thrown out. 
</P>
<P>
 C&S officials did not return a call for comment. 
</P>
