ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Irvine Sensors Corp.: The Costa Mesa company said Tuesday that it had won an 
18-month contract for $680,000 to build a three-dimensional chip stack for the 
Air Force. The company stacks memory chips on top of each other in a device the 
size of a sugar cube in order to save space in tiny electronics packages. In 
the contract with the Air Force's Phillips Laboratory, the Costa Mesa-based 
company will demonstrate a new way to package a variety of chips in the 
three-dimensional stack. 
</P>
